$ Distinguished Name
@ distinguished name

A *distinguished name* identifies an object in a hierarchical directory.

The *syntax* of distinguished names was orginally formulated in RFC 1779 («A String Representation of Distinguished Names») and
RFC 2253 («Lightweight Directory Access Protocol (v3): UTF-8 String Representation of Distinguished Names»)
(and then updated in RFC 4514 («Lightweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP): String Representation of Distinguished Names»).

